data.text:
It’s always a good time when Wiz Khalifa and Juicy J join forces.

Last month, they dropped their collab “Pop That Trunk” and now their back with “Backseat.” The single also features Project Pat. Theres a visual underway also, directed by Gabriel Hart. It’s set to drop tomorrow (Jan. 27). Wiz shared a clip, take a look:

https://www.instagram.com/p/CZL2P-5FLjW/

In 2016, Wiz and Juicy J dropped their first collab album, called, TGOD Mafia: Rude Awakening. It’s not clear when the new album will drop, Hip Hop DX points out it’ll be sometime later this year.
